Given relation  
R = { (−3, 9), (−2, 4), (−1, 1), (0, 0), (1, 1), (2, 4), (3, 9) }

a)  Is the relation a function?  
Yes.  Every first coordinate (x-value) appears exactly once, so each input has a single output. Therefore R is a function.

b)  Domain (all possible x-values)  
Domain(R) = { −3, −2, −1, 0, 1, 2, 3 }

c)  Range (all possible y-values)  
The y-values are 9, 4, 1, 0, 1, 4, 9.  Removing duplicates gives  
Range(R) = { 0, 1, 4, 9 }

